test-rating.description: GreatSchools Ratings for Louisiana are based on the 2012-2013 integrated Louisiana Educational Assessment Program (iLEAP), the Louisiana Educational Assessment Program for the 21st Century (LEAP 21) and End-Of-Course (EOC) test English language arts, math, science and social studies results. GreatSchools compared the test results for each grade and subject across all Louisiana schools and divided them into 1 through 10 ratings (10 is the best). Please note, private schools are not required to release test results, so ratings are available only for public schools. GreatSchools Ratings cannot be compared across states, because of differences in the states' standardized testing programs. Keep in mind that when comparing schools using GreatSchools Ratings it's important to factor in other information, including the quality of each school's teachers, the school culture, special programs, etc.
